16/10/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu said Friday (October 13th) that two candidates for the future post of Romanian European Commissioner should be named, one from each of the two senior government partners -- the National Liberal Party and the Democratic Party.
The European Parliament is expected to vote on the two new EC members from Bulgaria and Romania on January 4th, 2007, a few days after the countries join the EU.
(Adevarul, Romania Libera - 14/10/06)
